<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by funno:
[B]Been playing a cleric for a while, and have formulated a few rules. Granted im a 60th lvl 
HALFLING cleric. (this point will become evident in a min). But, again some simple little rules of the road.

setup:
I hardly ever go /anon or /rol, needless to say i get ALOT of tells. When I get these tells I do a /who all #####, if they are anon, then i ask them to unanon for a min.
I keep a legal pad and pen next to my computer.

Rules:
1) If you will not unanon, No rez for Joo.Period.

2) if your below lvl 35, sorry. suck it up, it builds character.

3) If I have to travel more than 2 zones, sorry, my widdle legs get tired. Sure RS3 helps, but still.

4) if im in the same zone as them, then they have to drag it to me, WITHOUT training me. DA and DB are wonderful for leaving their dumb a$$ there to take the rest of the train.

5) If they are a complete bonehead about me not helping them or give me grief in any form, I casualy write their name and guild name down on the afformentioned legal pad. 

6)if when i do the /who all, they come up on the "list" as its refered to. then No rez for Joo skippy.

7) i NEVER charge. dont even accept a donation. It is only mana, and time. but If they fit into my rules, then it doesnt really take that long. 

8) i forgot what eight was for...

9) if im in a group, rule 3 is voided, i wont leave, unless I know them, and they are a pretty decent person.

10) If they have EVER run up to me and asked for a sow or port before, they go onto the list. jk...I explain to them, that even though im a Halfling, im a cleric..and not all halflings with maces or sticks are druids. If they give me a hard time, They then go on the list. 

11) anyone who drags a corpse up and drops it at my feet from outta the blue. and then has the gall to say rez now, goes on the list. and promptly gets ignored. 

12) if they threaten me in anyway, they get on the list. cause, lets face it, a cleric is ALWAYS gonna get a group. it might take some time, but we are always welcome in a group. Its only a game, get over it. 

13) unlucky 13- ok i gotta throw this in, if VI every gets it in their heads that maybe SF wasnt the BEST place to put ragefire, i might break down and finnish my epic. yes thats right, i do NOT have my epic.

14) if in my journeys, i come across an unfortunate fellow's corpse, i will check the rez timer, and then check to see if said person is online. if they are, i send them a tell, saying hey, you need a rez. if they say yes, then Rez inc, if not, or no response, then i go on my merry way. 

15) All of the above rules can be tossed out the window, if i get the feeling they are in a bad way. or just to be nice. I have gone overland 3 contenants before to rez ppl, just cause they were having a bad time of it. see, im not a complete bastard.

I was using my /friends list for the spamheads who used to annoy me, but i find a list with a little jot of what they did to get onto the list works much better.

Funno Happykatz
HighPriest 
Guardians of the Keep
Drinal[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
